'''Hampstead''' is a satirical [[Interactive fiction|text adventure]] released for the [[ZX Spectrum]] and [[Commodore 64]].<ref name=i-hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad>{{Cite news|title='Hampstead': The social climbing game that has made the leap from ZX Spectrum to iPad|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/gaming/hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad-9504077.html|last=Osley|first=Richard|date=7 June 2014|access-date=6 May 2021|work=[[The Independent]]|last2=Green|first2=Chris}}</ref> The player begins the game in a filthy council flat, has to get a high-paying job in the city, woo a beautiful model and buy a house on [[Hampstead Heath]].<ref name=i-hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad/> It was written by Trevor Lever and Peter Jones.<ref name=i-hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad/> It sold about 70,000 copies.<ref name=i-hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad/>

==Legacy==
In 2014 a version was released for the [[iPad]].<ref name=i-hampstead-social-climbing-game-has-made-leap-zx-spectrum-ipad/>

